{{Unreferenced|date=January 2007}} {{Politics of the Democratic Republic of the Congo}} The '''Constitutional Court''' ({{Lang-fr|1='''Cour Constitutionnelle'''}}) was established by the [[Constitution of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|Constitution]] of the Third Republic on 18 February 2006. It is the highest constitutional authority in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
Its duty is to ensure that the principles and rules of the constitution are upheld. It considers conformity with the Constitution.
