'''Family patrimony''' is a type of [[Civil law (legal system)|civil law]] [[Property|patrimony]] that is created by [[marriage]] or [[civil union]] (where recognized) which creates a bundle of entitlements and [[obligation]]s that must be shared by the spouses or partners upon [[divorce]], [[annulment]], [[dissolution of marriage]] or dissolution of [[civil union]], when there must be a [[division of property]]. It is similar to the [[common law]] concept of [[community property]].

