{{about|a specific law report|law reports in general|Law report}} '''The Law Reports''' is the name of a series of [[law report]]s published by the [[Incorporated Council of Law Reporting]].
The Council maintains that they are "'the most authoritative reports' and should always be 'cited in preference where there is a choice'."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lawreports.co.uk/Publications/newlr.htm |title=The Law Reports - Cases Reported Index |publisher=The Incorporated Council of Law Reporting for England & Wales |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100116085250/http://www.lawreports.co.uk/Publications/newlr.htm |archivedate=January 16, 2010 |df= }}</ref> This series is now divided into four main sub-series: *Law Reports, Appeal Cases, covering decisions of the [[House of Lords]] (and, since 2009, the [[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom|Supreme Court]]), the [[Her Majesty's Most Honourable Privy Council|Privy Council]] and the Court of Appeal &ndash; started in 1866 as the Law Reports, English & Irish Appeals,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.H.L.&title=2305 |title=Law Reports, English & Irish Appeals |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105435/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.H.L.&title=2305 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> renamed in 1875<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.App.Cas.&title=707 |title=Law Reports, Appeal Cases (Second Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105444/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.App.Cas.&title=707 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> and redesigned in 1891;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=A.C.&title=28 |title=Law Reports, Appeal Cases (Third Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105456/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=A.C.&title=28 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> *Law Reports, Chancery Division, covering decisions of the Chancery Division of the High Court &ndash; started in 1865 as the Law Reports, Chancery Appeal Cases,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.Ch.App.&title=2300 |title=Law Reports, Chancery Appeal Cases |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105600/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.Ch.App.&title=2300 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> renamed in 1875<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Law+Rep.Ch.D.&title=2301 |title=Law Reports, Chancery Division (2nd Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105614/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Law+Rep.Ch.D.&title=2301 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> and redesigned in 1890;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Ch.&title=1578 |title=Law Reports, Chancery Division (3rd Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105627/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Ch.&title=1578 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> *Law Reports, Family Division, covering decisions of the [[High Court of Justice#Family Division|Family Division]] of the High Court &ndash; started in 1865 as the Law Reports, Probate & Divorce Cases,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.P.%26+D.&title=2310 |title=Law Reports, Probate & Divorce Cases |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> renamed Law Reports, Probate, Divorce & Admiralty Division in 1875,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=P.D.&title=2311 |title=Law Reports, Probate, Divorce & Admiralty Division |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105654/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=P.D.&title=2311 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> renamed Law Reports, Probate in 1891<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=P.&title=2312 |title=Law Reports, Probate |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105702/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=P.&title=2312 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> and renamed in 1972;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Fam.&title=1579 |title=Law Reports, Family Division |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105724/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Fam.&title=1579 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> and *Law Reports, Queen's Bench, covering decision of the [[High Court of Justice#Queen's Bench Division|Queen's Bench Division]] of the High Court &ndash; started in 1865,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.Q.B.&title=1581 |title=Law Reports, Queen's Bench (1st Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105901/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=L.R.Q.B.&title=1581 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> renamed Law Reports, Queen's Bench Division in 1875, renamed in 1891,<ref name="qb3">{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Q.B.&title=2314 |title=Law Reports, Queen's Bench (3rd Series) |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722105952/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=Q.B.&title=2314 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> renamed Law Reports, King's Bench in 1901<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=K.B.&title=1580 |title=Law Reports, King's Bench |work=Cardiff Index to Legal Abbreviations |publisher=[[Cardiff University]] |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722110012/http://www.legalabbrevs.cardiff.ac.uk/displaydetails?portal=false&abbr=K.B.&title=1580 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 |df= }}</ref> and renamed in 1952.<ref name="qb3"/>
==Series<ref>Glanville Williams, Learning the Law, Eleventh Edition, Stevens, 1982, page 39</ref>== The number and names of the series have changed. This is partly due to the merger of existing courts, the merger of existing divisions of individual courts, and the creation of new divisions of individual courts. [[Case citation|Citation]] of series has also changed.
===1865 to 1875=== The Law Reports were originally divided into eleven series. [[Glanville Williams]] said that "roughly speaking" there was a series for each of the [[superior court]]s.<ref>Glanville Williams, Learning the Law, Eleventh Edition, Stevens, 1982, page 37</ref> The series were:
*House of Lords, English and Irish Appeals *House of Lords, Scotch and Divorce Appeals *Privy Council Appeals *Chancery Appeal Cases *Equity Cases *Crown Cases Reserved *Queens Bench Cases *Common Pleas Cases *Exchequer Cases *Admiralty and Ecclesiastical Cases *Probate and Divorce Cases
House of Lords, English and Irish Appeals. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | HL | ... |}
House of Lords, Scotch and Divorce Appeals. These reports may be cited in the following ways:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | L.R. | ... | H.L.Sc. | ... |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | L.R. | ... | H.L.Sc. and Div. | ... |}
Privy Council Appeals. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | PC | ... |}
Chancery Appeal Cases. These reports may be cited in the following ways:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | Ch | ... |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | Ch App | ... |}
Equity Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | Eq | ... |}
[[Crown Cases Reserved]]. These reports may be cited in the following ways:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | CC | ... |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | CCR | ... |}
Queens Bench Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | QB | ... |}
Common Pleas Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | CP | ... |}
Exchequer Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | Ex | ... |}
Admiralty and Ecclesiastical Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | A & E | ... |}
Probate and Divorce Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! report ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | LR | ... | P & D | ... |}
===1875 to 1880=== In 1875, the number of series was reduced to six. This was due to the creation of the High Court and a decision on the part of the publishers, to put the House of Lords, the Privy Council and the new Court of Appeal in the same volume, and to group Crown Cases Reserved and the Queen's Bench Division together. The series were:
*Appeal Cases *Chancery Division *Queens Bench Division *Common Pleas Division *Exchequer Division *Probate Division
There was a change in the mode of citation. The abbreviation "LR" ceased to be used.
Appeal Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | App Cas | ... |}
Chancery Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | Ch D | ... |}
Queens Bench Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | QBD | ... |}
Common Pleas Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | CPD | ... |}
Exchequer Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | Ex D | ... |}
Probate Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | PD | ... |}
===1881 to 1890=== In 1881, the number of series was reduced to four. This is because the Common Pleas and Exchequer Divisions of the High Court were incorporated in the Queen's Bench Division of that court in 1880:
*Appeal Cases *Chancery Division *Queens Bench Division *Probate Division
Appeal Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | App Cas | ... |}
Chancery Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | Ch D | ... |}
Queens Bench Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | QBD | ... |}
Probate Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! (year of decision) ! volume ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | (...) | ... | PD | ... |}
===1891 onwards=== There have continued to be four series during this period, but their names have changed from time to time.
*Appeal Cases *Chancery Division *Queens Bench Division (1891 - 1901, 1952 onwards)/Kings Bench Division (1901 - 1952) (From 1907, this series included decisions of the [[Court of Criminal Appeal]] in place of the former [[Court for Crown Cases Reserved]].) *Probate (Replaced in 1972 by a series called Family, due to the creation of the Family Division of the High Court)
In 1891, there was a change in the mode of citation. Volumes published from 1891 onwards are cited by the year in which they were published and numbered according to the order of publication in that year, if more than one volume has been published in that year.
Appeal Cases. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | [...] | ... | AC | ... |}
Chancery Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | [...] | ... | Ch | ... |}
Queens Bench Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''R v Abbott'' | [1955] | 2 | QB | 497 |- valign="top" | ''R v Adams'' | [1980] | | QB | 575 |}
Kings Bench Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | [...] | ... | KB | ... |}
Probate Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | [...] | ... | P | ... |}
Family Division. These reports may be cited thus:
{| border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse;" |- bgcolor="#A4C8FF" valign="top" ! ''Style of cause'' ! [year of report] ! volume (if applicable) ! series ! page |- valign="top" | ''... v ...'' | [...] | ... | Fam | ... |}
